        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Form seems to validate unrequired elements when it should not.\n\n*Case in which this strange behavior occurs:*\n\n{code} \n$POSTDATA['name'] = 'x';\n$POSTDATA['age'] = ''; \/\/not required, but posted empty\nZend_Form->isValid($POSTDATA);\n{code}\n\n*What happens:*\nZend_Form validates age, because the array key was set\n\n*Expected behavior:*\nZend_Form skips age, because the value was empty\n\n*Possible fixes:*\n\n#1 Add a strict option to the method (backwards compatible)\n{code}\npublic function isValid(array $data, $strict = true) {\n        $valid = true;\n        foreach ($this->getElements() as $key => $element) {\n            if (!isset($data[$key])) {\n                if ($element->getRequired()) {\n                    $valid = $element->isValid(null, $data) && $valid;\n                }\n            } else {\n            \t\/\/Changed\n            \tif (($element->getRequired()) && ($data[$key] != '') && ($strict == false)) {\n                \t$valid = $element->isValid($data[$key], $data) && $valid;\n            \t} else {\n            \t\t$valid = $element->isValid($data[$key], $data) && $valid;\n            \t}\n            \t\/\/Change end\n            }\n        }\n\/\/ etc.. etc..*\/ \n}\n{code}\n\n#2 Just change the behavior\n\n{code}\npublic function isValid(array $data)\n{\n $valid = true;\n        foreach ($this->getElements() as $key => $element) {\n            if (!isset($data[$key])) {\n                if ($element->getRequired()) {\n                    $valid = $element->isValid(null, $data) && $valid;\n                }\n            } else {\n               \/\/Changed\n            \tif (($element->getRequired()) && ($data[$key] != '')) {\n                \t$valid = $element->isValid($data[$key], $data) && $valid;\n            \t} \n               \/\/Change end\n            }\n        }\n\/\/etc.. etc..\n{code}"
        },
