            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18947",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm assuming this behaviour was observed using the Preview Release, and not current trunk.\n\nEarlier this week (week of 3 Feb 2008), I added the ability to allow non-required values to be empty, and made this the default behaviour. To override that behaviour (i.e., make a non-required value also require validation when present), you must call:\n\n{code}\n$element->setAllowEmpty(false);\n{code}\n\nPlease verify what version of ZF you are using (preview release, snapshot (if so, which one), or current trunk).\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-08T06:46:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-08T06:46:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaapvstr",
                        "name": "jaapvstr",
                        "displayName": "jaap vstr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I first used the preview 1.5 release, then downloaded a snapshot to see if the problem was still there\nZendFramework-20080207-7833-en\n\nIt doesn't seem to be fixed in the latest snapshot either\nZendFramework-20080208-7862",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaapvstr",
                        "name": "jaapvstr",
                        "displayName": "jaap vstr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-08T07:01:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-08T07:01:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18952",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I cannot recreate the issue. I've got the following code:\n\n{code}\n$form = new Zend_Form();\n$form->addElement('text', 'username')->getElement('username')\n      \/\/ Note: the following line is unnecessary; elements are optional \n      \/\/ by default. Doing this simply to be explicit.\n      ->setRequired(false)  \n      ->addValidator('stringLength', false, array(1, 64));\n\n$data = array('username' => '');\n\nif (!$form->isValid($data)) {\n    var_export($form->getMessages());\n} else {\n    echo \"Form validated\";\n}\n{code}\n\nThe expected result is:\n\n{code}\nForm validated\n{code}\n\nAnd that's what I receive. Are you certain you are using code from the latest trunk (i.e., that you are pointing your include_path at the new snapshot you downloaded)?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-08T07:39:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-08T07:39:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18954",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaapvstr",
                        "name": "jaapvstr",
                        "displayName": "jaap vstr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oh, you're right, i get the same when linking to the snapshot version. \n\nI just looked for the fix, expecting it to be in the Zend_Form, but you fixed it in Zend_Form_Element.\n\nAnyway, great job on writing Zend_Form. I was quite disappointed that 1.0 didn't came with it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
